CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F376A1776435066
OL,3,CBin strikes, potholes and the Middle
OL,4,CEast: What's driving Birmingham voters
OL,6,FMore than half of voters (51%) said
OL,7,Fthey oppose the way the council has
OL,8,Fhandled the dispute, pointing to deep
OL,9,Fdissatisfaction with how the situation
OL,10,Fhas been managed.
OL,12,FWhen it comes to sympathy, residents
OL,13,Fare divided - but not evenly.
OL,15,FMore people said they side with Unite
OL,16,Fthe Union (28%) than with the council
OL,17,F(16%), suggesting striking workers
OL,18,Fhave a stronger level of public
OL,19,Fbacking.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G3/7
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
